/*!
@defgroup igf IGF: Input Glitch Filter
@details The MCUXpresso SDK provides a driver for the Input Glitch Filter (IGF)
module available on supported MCUXpresso SDK devices.

# Function groups {#IGFFunc}

The IGF driver supports configuration and control of glitch filtering on input signals.

## Initialization and Deinitialization {#IGFInit}
The function IGF_Init() initializes the IGF module and enables its clock.
The function IGF_Deinit() disables the IGF module and its clock.

## Default Configuration {#IGFDefault}
The function IGF_GetDefaultConfig() provides a default configuration structure
for the IGF module.

## Configuration {#IGFConfig}
The function IGF_SetIgfConfig() sets the IGF configuration for a specified channel.
Users can configure filter behavior, prescaler, thresholds, and polarity.

## Enable & Disable Filter {#IGFEnable}
The function IGF_Enable() enables or disables the glitch filter for a specified channel.

## Status {#IGFStatus}
The function IGF_GetStatusFlags() retrieves the status flags from the IGF module.
The function IGF_ClearStatusFlags() clears specified status flags.

*/